THE government said on Friday it’s a criminal offense to randomly hike prices of goods and commodities warning to take serious legal measures against all business people behind the criminal acts. Minister for Industry, Investment and Trade, Dr. Ashatu Kijaji told parliamentarians while tabling the ministry’s 99.1bil/- budget estimates and expenditures for the financial year 2022/23. She said prices of building materials including galvanized iron and steel bar have continued to climb high in line with increasing food prices in the country. Equally she said the average price of beans rose from 177,340/- per 100 kg in March 2021 to 188,294/- in 2022 and the average price of maize per 100 kg increased from 48,341/- to 59,861/-. “The average price of galvanized iron, 30 gauge rose to 27,714/- in March 2022 from 20,786/-,” the minister said. On the other hand she said that due to the effect of covid-19 pandemic and the war between Russia and Ukraine the price of cooking oil also kept increasing.